	},
	{
		type: "paragraph",
		text: "What makes speaking or writing a story or incident interesting is using descriptive words - words that add detail and colour to writing. They help to paint a picture of what is being described in the mind of the listener. These descriptive words are called adjectives. They are an important tool for effective communication, as they allow speakers and writers to convey their thoughts and ideas more precisely, making it easier for their audience to understand what they are talking about.",
	},
	{
		type: "paragraph",
		text: "For example, a description of a person's appearance might be followed by a comparison to another person in order to highlight similarities or differences between them. Similarly, a description of a product might be followed by a comparison to a competing product in order to help consumers make an informed choice.",
	},
	{
		type: "paragraph",
		text: "Descriptors or Adjectives are words that describe,",
	},
	
